-- Russian Fund Bids for Three Petroplus Refineries, Reuters Says
-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 2012-03-21T13:34:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/russian-fund-bids-for-three-petroplus-refineries-reuters-says.html
Fund Energy, a company founded by
Igor Yusufov, a former Russian energy minister and a member of
OAO Gazprom’s board of directors, is bidding for three Petroplus
Holdings AG’s refineries, Reuters reported.  The company is seeking to buy the Swiss refiner’s Cressier
site in  Switzerland , Coryton plant in the U.K. and Ingolstadt
facility in  Germany , according to Reuters, which cited an
unidentified person familiar with the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nidaa Bakhsh in London at 
